[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 1/50 done id=gsm8k_test_13 prediction='Let x be the number of vacuum cleaners Melanie started with.\n\n1. At the green house, she sold (1/3)x vacuum cleaners.\n2. After the green house, she had x - (1/3)x = (2/3)x vacuum cleaners left.\n3. She sold 2 more at the red house, so remaining after red house: (2/3)x - 2.\n4. At the orange house, she sold half of what was left, i.e., (1/2)[(2/3)x - 2].\n   After the orange house, she has the other half left: [(2/3)x - 2]/2.\n5. We know she has 5 vacuum cleaners left after all sales. So:\n   [(2/3)x - 2]/2 = 5\n6. Multiply both sides by 2:\n   (2/3)x - 2 = 10\n7. Add 2 to both sides:\n   (2/3)x = 12\n8. Multiply both sides by (3/2):\n   x = 12 * (3/2) = 18\n9. Check: Started with 18. Sold 6 at green (1/3 of' gold='18' correct=False
