[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 18/50 done id=gsm8k_test_407 prediction='Let’s break down the information step by step.\n\n1. Elliott’s goal is 10,000 steps per day.\n2. He finished half of his steps on walks to and from school.  \n   So, steps from school walks = ½ × 10,000 = 5,000 steps.\n3. He did another 1,000 steps with his friend.\n4. After that, he went for a jog and then had 2,000 steps remaining to reach his goal.\n5. First, calculate how many steps he had taken before the jog.  \n   Total goal = steps already taken + steps after jog + remaining steps  \n   10,000 = 5,000 (school) + 1,000 (friend) + steps during jog + 2,000 (remaining)  \n   5,000 + 1,000 = 6,000 steps before the jog and the jog itself.\n6. After the jog, he had 2,000 steps left. That means the steps he took during the jog plus the previous steps equal the total minus the remaining steps.  \n   So, steps before jog + steps during jog = 10,000 – 2,000 = 8,000 steps taken by the time' gold='2000' correct=False
